Major data loading steps: 1. Define a new object with a name (e.g., Reservoir) and type (node or link) 2. Define the attributes of the object (e.g., inflow and capacity) 3. Defind a master network (e.g., Logan City) and choose its domain (e.g., drinking water distribution) 4. Define a scenario network (e.g, existing network) 4. Create an instance of an object like a reservoir (e.g., Hyrum) 6. Connect the instance with the network scenario and the person who is adding the instance to the network scenarrio (e.g., your name) 7. Define metadata (e.g., source and unit) for the attribute to be linked to your instance 8. Connect the attribute metadata with the node instance network scenario at the Storage table to map out to the table where the data resides
